Package: streampress
Type: Package
Title: High-Performance Compressed Sparse Matrix I/O (.spz Format)
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-03-27
Authors@R: person("Zachary", "DeBruine",
    email = "zacharydebruine@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2234-4827"))
Description: Provides fast lossless (or lossy) compression of sparse matrices
    using the StreamPress (.spz) columnar format based on rANS entropy coding
    with delta-encoded indices. Achieves 5-10x compression over raw float32 CSC
    binary on typical single-cell RNA-seq count data and is faster to read than
    raw CSC because sparse object reconstruction is parallelised across
    independent chunks. Supports optional transpose storage for fast row access,
    row and column metadata tables (obs/var), dense matrix I/O with optional
    FP16/QUANT8 codecs, and partial column reads without full decompression.
    The .spz file format specification and C++ header-only library are available
    at <https://github.com/zdebruine/streampress>.
